   "body" : "This is basic info in the GUI that I've been wishing to have exposed for some time via the RPC and CLI without needing a bash workaround or script -- and for human users it would be good to have in `-getinfo`.\r\n\r\nRPC `getnetworkinfo`\r\n```\r\n  \"connections\": 15,\r\n  \"connections_in\": 6,\r\n  \"connections_out\": 9,\r\n```\r\n\r\n`bitcoin-cli -getinfo`\r\n```\r\n  \"connections\": {\r\n    \"in\": 6,\r\n    \"out\": 9,\r\n    \"total\": 15\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor `-getinfo` I also considered `\"connections\": \"15 (6 in, 9 out)\",` to save screen space, but a string value seemed less practical if anyone is parsing these as JSON.\r\n\r\nUpdate the tests, RPC help, and release notes for the changes. Also fixup the `getnettotals` timemillis help while touching `rpc/net.cpp`.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nReviewers can manually test this PR by [building from source](https://jonatack.github.io/articles/how-to-compile-bitcoin-core-and-run-the-tests), launching bitcoind, and then running `bitcoin-cli -getinfo`, `bitcoin-cli getnetworkinfo`, and `bitcoin-cli help getnetworkinfo`.\r\n",
